by (Olumide Ajanaku)¶

Introduction¶

The dataset i will be working with for this project is the Prosper Loan Data which contains different determinant factors that can affect loan outcome. The data contains 113937 rows and 81 columns.

Through my research for this project one thing that helped me understand this data well is the data variable definitions which i have attached below. https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1gDyi_L4UvIrLTEC6Wri5nbaMmkGmLQBk-Yx3z0XDEtI/edit?usp=sharing

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I am most interested in finding out the factors that affect the outcome of a loan.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

Data Cleaning¶

Quality Issues¶

Most of the dtypes are not accurate. For instance ListingNumber is an integer but we won't be performing calculations with it so it can be changed to object(string)

Define¶

  • i'll have to change the dtypes of some columns to the appopriate dtypes.

Code¶

In [164]:
#making all the datatype conversion here 
loan_clean['ListingNumber'] = loan_clean['ListingNumber'].astype(str)
loan_clean['ListingCreationDate'] = pd.to_datetime(loan_clean['ListingCreationDate'])
loan_clean['LoanOriginationDate'] = pd.to_datetime(loan_clean['LoanOriginationDate'])
loan_clean['ClosedDate'] = pd.to_datetime(loan_clean['ClosedDate'])
loan_clean['CreditGrade'] = loan_clean['CreditGrade'].astype('category')
loan_clean['LoanStatus'] = loan_clean['LoanStatus'].astype('category')
loan_clean['ProsperRating (Alpha)'] = loan_clean['ProsperRating (Alpha)'].astype('category')
loan_clean['ListingCategory (numeric)'] = loan_clean['ListingCategory (numeric)'].astype('category')
loan_clean['BorrowerState'] = loan_clean['BorrowerState'].astype('category')
loan_clean['Occupation'] = loan_clean['Occupation'].astype('category')
loan_clean['IncomeRange'] = loan_clean['IncomeRange'].astype('category')

#arrange the categorical columns that are ordinal in the right order

ordinal_var = {'ProsperRating (Alpha)':['AA', 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'HR'], 
             'IncomeRange':['$0', '$1-24,999', '$25,000-49,999', '$50,000-74,999', '$75,000-99,999',
                           '$100,000+']}
 
for var in ordinal_var:
    ordered_var = pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(ordered = True, categories = ordinal_var[var])
    loan_clean[var] = loan_clean[var].astype(ordered_var)
